Cryptocurrency Web Scraper

Description

This Python program fetches cryptocurrency market data from Yahoo Finance, extracts key details, and saves the data in XML, JSON, and an SQLite database. It provides a structured way to store and analyze market trends.

Features

Scrapes cryptocurrency data from Yahoo Finance.

Saves data in XML format.

Saves data in JSON format.

Stores the retrieved data in a SQLite database.

Handles errors and ensures data consistency.

Files

yahoo_crypto.py (Main script)

crypto_data.xml (Output XML file)

crypto_data.json (Output JSON file)

crypto_data.db (SQLite database storing scraped data)

How to Run

Prerequisites

Ensure you have Python installed on your system.
Install required dependencies using:

pip install requests beautifulsoup4 sqlite3

Execution

Run the following command in the terminal:

python yahoo_crypto.py

Example Output

Data is extracted from Yahoo Finance and saved in structured formats (XML, JSON, and SQLite).

Future Enhancements

Integrate real-time API updates.

Add support for multiple cryptocurrencies.

Enhance error handling and logging.

Implement a web interface for data visualization.

